The paper focuses on using deep learning techniques to recognize facial emotions, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves training a model to recognize emotions, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of real-world facial images also suggests a potential connection to multimedia (cs.MM) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-categories.
